<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">
In North Africa, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[382,524,550,575]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Esolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis box="[382,524,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">E. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[718,822,549,575]" name="Morocco" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[830,917,549,575]" name="Algeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1059,549,575]" name="Tunisia" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1182,549,575]" name="Algeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, the species is reported from the northern part of the country in Mazafran, and Chéllif (
<collectingRegion box="[856,920,585,612]" country="Algeria" name="Blida" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Blida</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Arab, A." box="[941,1066,585,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" refId="ref8441" refString="Arab, A. (2004) Recherches faunistiques et ecologiques sur les reseaux hydrographiques du Chelif et du bassin versant du Mazafran. These de Doctorat d'Etat, Universite des Sciences et de la Technologie Houari Boumediene. Faculte des Sciences Biologiques, Alger, Algerie, 171 pp." type="book" year="2004">Arab 2004</bibRefCitation>
), and in the north-east from Ghar Rouban (
<collectingCountry box="[256,315,621,647]" name="Algeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Oran</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Berthelemy, C." box="[339,541,621,648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" pagination="244 - 285" refId="ref8801" refString="Berthelemy, C. (1964) Elminthidae d'Europe occidentale et meridionale et d'Afrique du Nord (Coleopteres). Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Toulouse, 99 (1 - 2), 244 - 285." type="journal article" year="1964">Berthélemy 1964</bibRefCitation>
). In Kabylia, the species is recorded from the Djurdjura massif (
<bibRefCitation author="Ait Mouloud, S." pageId="8" pageNumber="110" refId="ref8347" refString="Ait Mouloud, S. (1988) Essais de recherches sur la derive des macro-invertebres dans l'oued Aissi: faunistique, ecologie et biogeographie. These de Magister, Universite des Sciences et de la Technologie Houari Boumediene. Institut des Sciences de la Nature, d'Alger, Algerie, 118 pp." type="book" year="1988">Aït Mouloud 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lounaci-Daoudi, D." box="[222,471,657,683]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" refId="ref10820" refString="Lounaci-Daoudi, D. (1996) Travaux sur la faunistique, l'ecologie et la biogeographie des insectes du reseau hydrographique du Sebaou. These de Magister, Universite de Tizi-Ouzou, Algerie, 152 pp." type="book" year="1996">Lounaci-Daoudi 1996</bibRefCitation>
; Lounaci 2005).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">
In this study, it was found extremely rarely in only middle-reach streams, with intermittent flow, located at altitudes between 
<quantity box="[356,428,729,755]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="160.0">160 m</quantity>
and 
<specimenCount box="[485,564,729,755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" type="generic">
<quantity box="[485,560,729,755]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
The two sites are impacted by domestic water pollution and sand and gravel extraction. In 
<collectingCountry box="[310,377,765,791]" name="Spain" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Spain</collectingCountry>
, this taxon is considered relatively tolerant of organic pollution (Garcia-Críado &amp; Fernández- Aláez 1995).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[230,328,837,863]" name="Slovakia" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[336,480,838,863]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Esolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis box="[336,480,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">E. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
prefers hyporhithral to epipotamal reaches of streams and smaller rivers in lowlands and hills around 
<quantity box="[346,410,873,899]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="300.0">300m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<bibRefCitation author="Ciampor, F. &amp; Zatovicova, Z." box="[489,830,872,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" pagination="218" refId="ref9188" refString="Ciampor, F. &amp; Zatovicova, Z. (2004) First record of Esolus pygmaeus (Coleoptera, Elmidae) from Slovakia. Biologia, 59, 218." type="journal article" year="2004">Čiampor &amp; Zaťovičová 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[884,977,873,899]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Czechia</collectingCountry>
, the species is considered very rare and endangered (
<bibRefCitation author="Boukal, D. S. &amp; Boukal, M. &amp; Fikacek, M. &amp; Hajek, J. &amp; Klecka, J. &amp; Skalicky, S. &amp; Stastny, J. &amp; Travnicek, D." box="[296,519,909,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 289" refId="ref8994" refString="Boukal, D. S., Boukal, M., Fikacek, M., Hajek, J., Klecka, J., Skalicky, S. Stastny, J. &amp; Travnicek, D. (2007) Katalog vodnich brouku Ceske republiky-Catalogue of water beetles of the Czech Republic. Klapalekiana, 43 (Supplementum), 1 - 289." type="journal article" year="2007">
Boukal 
<emphasis box="[386,436,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). However, in 
<collectingCountry box="[684,788,909,935]" name="Morocco" pageId="8" pageNumber="110">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, the species is widely distributed in the main areas of the country, where it inhabits headwaters, middle-reach streams, and is rarely found in lowlands, at altitudes between 
<quantity box="[151,208,981,1007]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="10.0">10 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[262,347,981,1007]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8199999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="1820.0">1820 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bennas, N. &amp; Sainz-Cantero, C. E." box="[362,708,981,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" pagination="61 - 79" refId="ref8596" refString="Bennas, N. &amp; Sainz-Cantero, C. E. (2007) Nouvelles donnees sur les Coleopteres aquatiques du Maroc: les Elmidae Curtis, 1830 et les Dryopidae Billberg, 1820 du Rif (Coleoptera). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 24 (1), 61 - 79." type="journal article" year="2007">Bennas &amp; Sáinz-Cantero 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benamar, L." box="[720,889,980,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="110" refId="ref8555" refString="Benamar, L. (2015) Les Coleopteres aquatiques du Maroc: atlas, biogeographie et degre de vulnerabilite. These de Doctorat d'etat en Sciences, Universite Abdelmalek Essaadi, Faculte des Sciences, Tetouan, 538 pp." type="book" year="2015">Benamar 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
